Detailed Description

A scalar node is an opaque datum that can be presented as a series of zero or more Unicode scalar values.

Example: Adena

Gets the value of this node as a StringRef.

Parameters
Storageis used to store the content of the returned StringRef iff it requires any modification from how it appeared in the source. This happens with escaped characters and multi-line literals.
